ce:section.ce:para:
After homogenizing the mixed powders by the above methods, the composites were examined by thermal desorption mass spectroscopy (TDS) (Anelva M-QA200TS) combined with thermogravimetry (TG) (Rigaku TG8120) upon heating up to 450 ° C with a heating rate of 5 ° C/min. This equipment was especially designed and built up for using it inside the glovebox filled with purified argon, which permitted simultaneous measurements by TG and TDS without exposing the samples to air. We examined the structural characters of the produced composites by X-ray diffraction (XRD) measurements (Rigaku RINT2000, Cu K
α
).
